The screen shows a web development instructional video, likely focused on the CanvasRenderingContext2D API in JavaScript. The main area displays a code editor with HTML and JavaScript code related to drawing an ellipse on a canvas. A small, rectangular canvas is visible on the right side of the screen displaying an incomplete ellipse (a curved line segment). The UI indicates use of MDN Web Docs, with tabs for "References", "Examples", and "Specifications".

```html
<canvas id="canvas" width="200" height="200"></canvas>
```

```javascript
const canvas = document.getElementById("canvas");
const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");

// Draw the ellipse
ctx.beginPath();
ctx.arc(100, 100, 58, 75, Math.PI * 4, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the ellipse's line of reflection
ctx.beginPath();
ctx.strokeStyle = [5, 51];
ctx.moveTo(0, 200);
ctx.lineTo(200, 0);
ctx.stroke();
```

